{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-sermons-list-js","path":"/en/sermons/page/917","result":{"pageContext":{"pagination":{"total":1038,"current":917},"lang":"en","nodes":[{"id":"20763","title":"Six Words Every Physician Should Know","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/conferences/1/50/50/2019-AMEN-LOGO.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Amarachi Nwankpah"}],"duration":1732.1,"recordingDate":"2019-11-01T09:30:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/71671/2019/10/20763/20191101-0930-20763-823ebaa4148aeda9c6736ccf5dd0a8da-96k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/71672/2019/10/20763/20191101-0930-20763-823ebaa4148aeda9c6736ccf5dd0a8da-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/71673/2019/10/20763/20191101-0930-20763-823ebaa4148aeda9c6736ccf5dd0a8da-16k.mp3"}],"description":"<p>OBJECTIVES At the conclusion of this CME activity, the learner should be better able to: 1. Understand the barriers that hamper or destroy the physician's effectiveness in patient care. 2. Recognize that spirituality is a core patient need and its beneficial influences on health. 3. Understand the role spirituality can play in their professional growth, promotion of personal happiness, and the basis of their calling as a physician.</p>"},{"id":"20764","title":"Evaluating the Final Impressions","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/conferences/1/50/50/2019-AMEN-LOGO.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Kianna Simmons"}],"duration":3122,"recordingDate":"2019-11-01T10:45:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/71668/2019/10/20764/20191101-1045-20764-825267b35bb59bc5c9a72691775c23a5-96k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/71669/2019/10/20764/20191101-1045-20764-825267b35bb59bc5c9a72691775c23a5-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/71670/2019/10/20764/20191101-1045-20764-825267b35bb59bc5c9a72691775c23a5-16k.mp3"}],"description":"<p>OBJECTIVES 1. Understand the greatest impressions are the ones we make, not the ones we take. 2. Explore how 'Christ in You' is attainable for everyone. 3. Share through testimony the outcomes of 'Christ in You' impressions. 4. Demonstrate how practicing 'Christ in You' will improve relationships with patients and subsequently inspire lasting change.</p>"},{"id":"20761","title":"Us in Christ and Christ in Us","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/persons/_/50/50/schwartz_brian.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Brian Schwartz"}],"duration":2895.2,"recordingDate":"2019-10-31T19:00:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/71654/2019/10/20761/20191031-1900-20761-1ae1c38a3261cc4e4765c377a55945b9-96k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/71655/2019/10/20761/20191031-1900-20761-1ae1c38a3261cc4e4765c377a55945b9-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/71656/2019/10/20761/20191031-1900-20761-1ae1c38a3261cc4e4765c377a55945b9-16k.mp3"}],"description":"<p>OBJECTIVES 1. Identify the significant role spiritual care plays in healthcare. 2. Describe the importance of having &lsquo;Christ In You&rsquo; and how our personal relationship with Jesus is the foundation to effectively engage in whole-person care. 3. Demonstrate how adding a spiritual component to your practice leads to improved physical outcomes. 4. </p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Inspire attendees to live a life committed to reflecting 'Christ in You' on a daily basis as they care for their patients physically, mentally, and spiritually. Many of our family members, our patients, and our colleagues feel an emptiness, and whether they know it or not, this can only be filled by Christ. We will look at Philippians 2 and identify with Christ as we 'let this mind be in you'. We will apply this and other passages to our calling as healthcare workers and as Adventist believers who are anticipating Christ's soon return.&nbsp;</p>"},{"id":"20737","title":"The Arrogance of Knowledge","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/persons/_/50/50/grabiner_steven2.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Steven Grabiner"}],"duration":2203.8,"recordingDate":"2019-10-05T12:00:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/71236/2019/10/20737/20191005-1200-20737-4fe34a3e93d2fb35d07868dd3d80b5f7-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/71237/2019/10/20737/20191005-1200-20737-4fe34a3e93d2fb35d07868dd3d80b5f7-16k.mp3"}],"description":"<p>Our biblical knowledge can lead to arrogance without God's motivating love</p>"},{"id":"20708","title":"Priorities","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/persons/_/50/50/Morgan_Garhett.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"Garhett Morgan"}],"duration":2369.2,"recordingDate":"2018-10-06T11:30:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/70972/2019/10/20708/20181006-1130-20708-8d3444a0aa942bf7a1979b8270f5c8e5-96k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/70973/2019/10/20708/20181006-1130-20708-8d3444a0aa942bf7a1979b8270f5c8e5-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/70974/2019/10/20708/20181006-1130-20708-8d3444a0aa942bf7a1979b8270f5c8e5-16k.mp3"}],"description":""},{"id":"20202","title":"Sanctuary, Salvation and Our Savior: Altar of Incense","imageWithFallback":{"url":"https://s.audioverse.org/english/gallery/persons/_/50/50/Shin_David.jpg"},"persons":[{"name":"David Shin"}],"duration":2642.9,"recordingDate":"2019-04-06T11:00:00.000Z","audioFiles":[{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/68719/2019/07/20202/20190406-1100-20202-fa91431f9df75b6c666931e5a708d22c-96k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/english/download/dl/68720/2019/07/20202/20190406-1100-20202-fa91431f9df75b6c666931e5a708d22c-48k.mp3"},{"url":"https://www.audioverse.org/en